&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;Slingshot is seeking a polymer scientist/engineer to join our team in a full-time capacity. This is a high-impact role at the intersection of chemistry, materials science, biology and instrumentation - offering a chance to shape the technical roadmap for products that will positively impact human health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;As a key contributor to our R&amp;amp;D efforts, you will lead technical strategy, design and conduct complex experiments, and translate experimental insights into meaningful innovations. You will work alongside a multidisciplinary team, and ensure that our R&amp;amp;D milestones drive the company&#39;s overall mission forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;This position is ideal for a self-motivated individual with a proactive, can-do attitude who thrives in a fast-paced, collaborative environment. Join us at a critical stage of development as we push the boundaries of advanced polymer manufacturing. You will have the opportunity to shape a novel high-throughput platform, lead technical reviews, and influence key decisions with long-term impact on our technology roadmap.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; This is an on-site position based in Emeryville, California.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and develop new polymer chemistry and formulations for innovative synthetic cell products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ownership of technical projects, designing and conducting rigorous experiments&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the technical strategy for scale-up, validation, and optimization of polymer manufacturing systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technical reviews and contribute proof-of-concept data to inform critical strategic decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform bench-scale scale-up studies and validation studies, such as variability, reproducibility, and stability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive innovation by collaborating cross-functionally to optimize the interplay between polymer chemistry, hardware, and production processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set up, operate, and troubleshoot laboratory hardware, fluidic components, and analytical instrumentation.&lt;/li&gt;
